{
  "texts": [
    "There are two ways to do this.",
    "Firstly, by iteratively applying community detection to each topic sub-graph, CT discovers the next level of the topic hierarchy.",
    "This can be done to a specified depth or we can allow CT to uncover the entire hierarchy by stopping the growth of the topic tree once the produced sub-topics are smaller than three terms.",
    "An example of 3 levels of topics discovered on the BBC corpus is show in Fig. 6.",
    "The level 1 topics correspond to the 5 article categories of the corpus.Level 2 (in green) and then 3 (in orange) show increasingly specific sub-topics."
  ]
}